FBIS3-53742 "drnes012_n_94008" FBIS-NES-94-012 Document Type:Daily Report 19 Jan 1994 LEBANON Amal-Israel Clashes Occur in Southern Areas UN Soldier Wounded in by Israelis NC1701112394 Kafr Killa Voice of the South in Arabic 1030 GMT 17 Jan 94 NC1701112394 Kafr Killa Voice of the South Language: Arabic Article Type:BFN [Text] An explosive charge went off on the al-Shumariyah road this morning, causing no casualties. Meanwhile, a UN soldier was wounded when a UN post in 'Alman came under terrorist shell fire. [Paris AFP in English at 1027 GMT on 17 January in a Tyre-datelined report, says: "A Finnish peacekeeper was wounded by Israeli shelling in south Lebanon Monday, a UN officer said. "The soldier, who was not named, was slightly hurt when a 155 mm mortar [as received] shell fired from inside Israel's self-declared security zone in south Lebanon exploded near a UN position, said the officer from the UN Interim Force in Lebanon (UNIFIL). "The shelling began after a bomb attack on a patrol from Israel's proxy South Lebanon Army (SLA) militia, which caused no casualties. "SLA and Israeli forces retaliated by shelling nearby villages outside the zone where Iranian-backed Hizballah guerrillas are based."]
